title: Slow Cooker Pork Ramen
summary: Need a dairy free main course? Slow Cooker Pork Ramen could be an awesome recipe to try. For $1.58 per serving, this recipe covers 23% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. One serving contains 251 calories, 24g of protein, and 13g of fat. 30 people were impressed by this recipe. A mixture of soy sauce, salt and pepper, ginger, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so tasty. To use up the soy sauce you could follow this main course with the Panna Cotta with Strawberry-Vin Santo Sauce as a dessert. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes about 8 hours and 15 minutes. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 69%. This score is pretty good. Try Slow-Cooker Gingered Pork and Ramen Noodles, Slow Cooker Japanese Pork and Ramen Soup, and Slow Cooker Ramen Soup for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Ramen Noodles on the menu? Try pairing with Riesling, Sake, and Sauvignon Blanc. Saké is an obvious choice when it comes to Japanese food. If you want to stick to grape wine, though, you might opt for sauvignon blanc or riesling. The Louis Guntrum Dry Riesling with a 4.4 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 15 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.title: Louis Guntrum Dry Riesling
productMatches.description: The 2016 Louis Guntrum Dry Riesling has a delicate fragrance of white peaches, apricot and juicy pears. Impressive mouthfeel, and lasting flavors. The classical Riesling in expression and elegance.

instructions: Make the BrothHeat oil in a cast iron skillet over medium high heat. Sprinkle pork shoulder with salt and pepper. Sear pork in cast iron skillet for about 2-3 minutes per side. Place pork in slow cooker. Add remaining broth ingredients. Cook on low for 7-8 hours until the pork is extremely tender and falling apart. Remove pork and shred. Strain broth to remove all the solids.Build the BowlsPrepare the toppings while the broth is cooking. To build a bowl, place noodles in the bottom of a bowl and ladle broth on top. Top each bowl with a shredded pork, broccoli, soft boiled eggs, sliced green onions and a splash of sriracha and soy sauce. Serve and enjoy!
